22/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- The main opposition Socialist Party (SP) filed a lawsuit Monday (March 21st) against Interior Minister Lulzim Basha, accusing him in connection with the deaths of four protestors during a January 21st anti-government rally.
The SP also accuses state police head Hysni Burgaj and the head of Tirana police Sajmir Mucaj.
The actual perpetrators remain unknown.
The lawsuit is signed by 25 lawmakers.
Basha is running for mayor of Tirana against the SP incumbent, Edi Rama.
(Top Channel, Alsat, Klan, Vizion +, Balkan Web - 21/03/11)
